@PR Betz — Totally agree. Enough with the pop culture and gaming clues. And stop with the cutesy SUHWEET stuff, too. Maybe the editors just figure this is where we’re at, that this is what appeals to the masses. Or maybe it’s just a blind spot on the part of the constructors.

I’ve been doing crosswords from the archives from the 1990s, and they are much more balanced with literature and other (what should be) general knowledge clues. There are some current events from that time, but my memory is still good enough to get those. These puzzles can be a bit more difficult with their wordplay, but enjoyably so — I can’t say that for what I see here some of the time. 

I also agree with those who question the inclusion of the Cardi B song. Would that have flown back in the day? Somehow, I doubt it.

